<section id="security" class="px-6 py-24 lg:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <div class="grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Left: explanation -->
      <div>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">
          Capability-Based Security
        </p>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
          If you didn't grant it,<br />it doesn't exist.
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted">
          <p>
            Most systems bolt security on top: sandboxes, policies, permission dialogs. An
            agent runs inside your OS and you <em>hope</em> the guardrails hold. A prompt
            injection attack, a confused deputy, a privilege escalation&mdash;and the cage
            opens.
          </p>
          <p>
            InferNode works differently. Each agent gets its own namespace&mdash;a view of the
            world constructed from only the resources you explicitly mount. Try to access
            something you weren't given? It doesn't error. It simply
            <strong class="text-text">does not exist</strong>. There is no attack surface
            because there is no surface.
          </p>
          <p>
            This isn't a claim. The isolation model has been
            <strong class="text-text">formally verified</strong> using TLA+, SPIN, and CBMC.
            Mathematical proof, not just testing. Show your auditors the math.
          </p>
          <p>
            Because agents are provably contained, you can give them
            <strong class="text-text">more freedom</strong>&mdash;more tools, more data, more
            autonomy&mdash;without more risk. Safe agents are productive agents.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: terminal visualization -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface font-mono text-sm overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border px-4 py-3">
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-rpi/60"></div>
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-llm/60"></div>
          <div class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-node-jetson/60"></div>
          <span class="ml-2 text-xs text-text-muted">agent namespace</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 space-y-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # Grant the agent access to docs and LLM</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> mount /n/docs /agent/data</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> mount /n/llm /agent/llm</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # Agent can see docs and LLM</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> ls /agent/</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-node-laptop">data/</span>
            <span class="text-node-llm ml-4">llm/</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # Your credentials, email, SSH keys?</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> ls /home/ /credentials/ /email/</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted italic">
              &nbsp;&nbsp;# nothing. they don't exist in this namespace.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted"> # Prompt injection tried to read SSH keys?</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">;</span>
            <span class="text-text"> cat /home/.ssh/id_rsa</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted italic">
              &nbsp;&nbsp;# nothing to cat. the path doesn't exist.
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
